      "type": "summary",
      "content": "In this lesson, we saw 'shi' appearing twice in the final poem. In 'ききし' (kikishi), it modifies the time/circumstance of hearing. In 'おもはざりし' (omohazarishi), it modifies the unspoken situation before the particle 'o' (which can act like a noun-placeholder). In both cases, 'shi' anchors a memory to a specific concept or moment."
